00:26:05.074 --> 00:26:06.074
[Laughter]
&gt;&gt; Baratunde Thurston: Uh, so I wanna talk

00:26:06.074 --> 00:26:07.074
about that process.

00:26:07.074 --> 00:26:08.074
You know, give a little behind the scenes
of the writing process.

00:26:08.074 --> 00:26:09.074
And this is the sort of, uh, the route that
I came up with.

00:26:09.074 --> 00:26:10.074
I tried to write this book in summer of 2010,
I sort of missed my target.

00:26:10.074 --> 00:26:11.074
I told you about the reengineering around
memoir, so summer 2011 was it.

00:26:11.074 --> 00:26:12.074
I had a drop dead deadline, July 15th.

00:26:12.074 --> 00:26:13.074
And those last four weeks, this was all I
did.

00:26:13.074 --> 00:26:14.074
I woke up, I ate, I wrote, I biked into work,
I took a break, I wrote, I took another break,

00:26:14.074 --> 00:26:15.074
I wrote, I biked home and kind of wash, rinse,
repeat.

00:26:15.074 --> 00:26:16.074
I also wanted to play with the community of
people who knew this book was coming.

00:26:16.074 --> 00:26:17.074
Folks who were interested in what I had to
do.

00:26:17.074 --> 00:26:18.074
So I was trying to use the web in some interesting
ways.

00:26:18.074 --> 00:26:19.074
When I did the interviews I would check in
on four square and use the hash tag how to

00:26:19.074 --> 00:26:20.074
be black.

00:26:20.074 --> 00:26:25.820
I was sharing snippets of what I wrote on
Facebook and on my Google plus page.

00:26:25.820 --> 00:26:29.940
And so this was a chapter I wrote about what
It means, “How to be the black employee.”

00:26:29.940 --> 00:26:33.809
And folks were just really, you know, we had
a lot of good feedback, uh, on that early

00:26:33.809 --> 00:26:34.809
moment.

00:26:34.809 --> 00:26:37.509
Even as I was writing I was like, “Okay,
is this gonna write my sort of how to be black

00:26:37.509 --> 00:26:39.739
beta project?”

00:26:39.739 --> 00:26:44.190
I also got some amazing feedback and I wanna
share just a few slices of what people had

00:26:44.190 --> 00:26:47.349
to say as they looked over my virtual shoulder.

00:26:47.349 --> 00:26:53.309
Some woman said, “This book is clearly not
written for black folks.

00:26:53.309 --> 00:26:56.129
It’s too wordy and there’s no pictures.”

00:26:56.129 --> 00:26:58.909
That was one of my Facebook fans that wrote
that.

00:26:58.909 --> 00:27:03.809
So I wrote her back and saying, “Can someone
please translate this for me?

00:27:03.809 --> 00:27:05.879
I can’t understand it without pictures.”

00:27:05.879 --> 00:27:07.869
Uh, so that was pretty interesting.

00:27:07.869 --> 00:27:12.059
Someone else wrote, “This book is solely
based on ignorance.

00:27:12.059 --> 00:27:14.799
Martin Luther King, Junior would be ashamed
if he read this.

00:27:14.799 --> 00:27:17.379
Good job with settin us back fifty years,
dick.”

00:27:17.379 --> 00:27:19.469
[Laughter]
&gt;&gt; Baratunde Thurston: There’s a lot to

00:27:19.469 --> 00:27:20.469
unpack from that.

00:27:20.469 --> 00:27:23.580
First of all, he has a direct channel with
the ghost of Martin Luther King, which I think

00:27:23.580 --> 00:27:25.960
is amazing that we haven’t heard from this
dude before.

00:27:25.960 --> 00:27:29.029
I also like that he called me a dick, that’s
really nice.

00:27:29.029 --> 00:27:30.029
That’s really nice.

00:27:30.029 --> 00:27:32.409
But mostly I like how he spelled “solely.”

00:27:32.409 --> 00:27:34.179
S-O-U-L-Y, which is kinda black.

00:27:34.179 --> 00:27:36.519
[Laughter]
&gt;&gt; Baratunde Thurston: And I was like, “Maybe

00:27:36.519 --> 00:27:38.139
I should listen to this dude.

00:27:38.139 --> 00:27:42.820
