00:29:13.860 --> 00:29:14.860
I was in high school.

00:29:14.860 --> 00:29:18.179
And someone said, “You should call it Going
Black to Africa” And I was like, “Obviously,

00:29:18.179 --> 00:29:19.179
I should.”

00:29:19.179 --> 00:29:20.179
And so I did.

00:29:20.179 --> 00:29:24.169
And I don’t know who that was, it was like
chatuser0056, but uh, they get a little credit

00:29:24.169 --> 00:29:26.629
for making the book even blacker.

00:29:26.629 --> 00:29:29.799
Uh, so this is what people had to say as they
were in the chat room.

00:29:29.799 --> 00:29:34.289
“This is really what the internet is all
about, gives me a connection with the author.”

00:29:34.289 --> 00:29:37.519
“How self-obsessed does one have to be to
set something like this up?”

00:29:37.519 --> 00:29:39.429
[Laughter]
&gt;&gt; Baratunde Thurston: The answer is very.

00:29:39.429 --> 00:29:41.159
[Laughter]
&gt;&gt; Baratunde Thurston: Uh, I have a lot of

00:29:41.159 --> 00:29:42.159
self-love.

00:29:42.159 --> 00:29:44.619
“Update them to theme and I’ll leave you
alone.”

00:29:44.619 --> 00:29:48.299
A lot of people were obsessed with typos during
live writing.

00:29:48.299 --> 00:29:50.059
I’m like, “I will go back and fix those.”

00:29:50.059 --> 00:29:51.559
[Laughs]
&gt;&gt; Baratunde Thurston: We have editors and

00:29:51.559 --> 00:29:54.379
copy editors, like, please don’t get caught
up on it.

00:29:54.379 --> 00:29:56.880
But a lot of people have a little OCD about
the spelling.

00:29:56.880 --> 00:29:59.980
“I’ve watched cartoonists before, but
this is very different.”

00:29:59.980 --> 00:30:03.450
“Just the little I’ve read here makes
me want to buy this book.”

00:30:03.450 --> 00:30:04.450
Yes!

00:30:04.450 --> 00:30:05.450
Good.

00:30:05.450 --> 00:30:07.169
I should follow up and make sure they did
it and they weren’t just lying.

00:30:07.169 --> 00:30:08.730
“I have an urge to tweet about this.”

00:30:08.730 --> 00:30:09.730
Good.

00:30:09.730 --> 00:30:11.089
“It’s interesting to see his writing flow.”

00:30:11.089 --> 00:30:14.759
“I’m surprised to see Baratunde use semi-colons.”

00:30:14.759 --> 00:30:15.979
Which again I’m like, “Why?

00:30:15.979 --> 00:30:17.279
Is it cause I’m black?

00:30:17.279 --> 00:30:18.279
Like, I don’t understand.”

00:30:18.279 --> 00:30:19.599
[Laughter]
&gt;&gt; Baratunde Thurston: Like, “Is that, am

00:30:19.599 --> 00:30:20.769
