00:43:58.299 --> 00:44:03.470
Um, my middle name is Rafiq, R-A-F-I-Q, which
means friend or companion.

00:44:03.470 --> 00:44:07.240
And my last name is Thurston which means that
was the guy that owned my people.

00:44:07.240 --> 00:44:10.329
[Laughter]
&gt;&gt; Baratunde Thurston: Um, so my name in comb--.

00:44:10.329 --> 00:44:14.210
Baratunde Rafiq in combination is supposed
to mean kingly companion.

00:44:14.210 --> 00:44:16.609
That was what my mother was going for.

00:44:16.609 --> 00:44:21.220
Yeah, and I don’t, I don’t really have
patience for the black card being pulled thing.

00:44:21.220 --> 00:44:24.200
And, uh, I know I’m black.

00:44:24.200 --> 00:44:26.539
[Laughs]
&gt;&gt; Baratunde Thurston: And I think the self-knowledge

00:44:26.539 --> 00:44:32.720
and the confidence to not be buffeted by the
external pressures from all kinds of people.

00:44:32.720 --> 00:44:34.549
You know, there's this weird identity matrix,
right?

00:44:34.549 --> 00:44:38.470
Where there’s like who you are and who the
world expects you to be, whether you’re

00:44:38.470 --> 00:44:41.680
a woman, whether you’re black, whether you’re
gay, whether you’re white dude, whatever.

00:44:41.680 --> 00:44:43.760
There’s always a gap in those things.

00:44:43.760 --> 00:44:48.140
And within the black matrix, there’s inside
the black community, “You’re not black

00:44:48.140 --> 00:44:51.940
